channel.title: RSC++ Managed Edition!
channel.description:
This update precedes all those below the line. After much consideration I have scrapped that server and started over. There was just way too much horrible coding in that one. Once RSC++ Managed Edition V2 is operational you can expect everything below the line to be discarded to make way for new updates. [hr]
Well this is just a topic letting everyone know that I have restarted my RSC++ project from 10? months ago. This time its purely managed code. Unfortunately I dont have much more for news right now since I havent even ran the damn thing but its near completion. Expect an update with much more information in the next couple days =]
[br][br][size=1]Posted on: April 05, 2008, 02:57:27 PM[/size][hr]Just a quick update to this project...I seem to be having a slight problem with filling my in stream but hopefully it will be fixed by the end of the day and ill be able to provide some screenshots of it running at the least.[br][br][size=1]Posted on: April 05, 2008, 08:12:41 PM[/size][hr]Not that anyone can see this topic anymore because I cant bump my own topics :< but another small update...Filling my in stream now works correctly. Just having another stupid problem with a login packet size of 0 -_____-[br][br][size=1]Posted on: April 05, 2008, 10:23:58 PM[/size][hr]Alrighty so all the login stuff now works...problem now is just getting a black screen when logging in :>
Have I mentioned how much I hate Managed C++ yet?[br][br][size=1]Posted on: April 05, 2008, 10:53:44 PM[/size][hr]Screenshot of the crap ass progress -_- http://i260.photobucket.com/albums/ii7/AridTag/RSC.jpg (I removed the IMG tags to shrink the post size for my newest update!)
[size=1]Posted on: April 07, 2008, 12:48:26 AM[/size][hr] HUGE UPDATE!!! (so huge it needed the caps lock) [IMG]http://i260.photobucket.com/albums/ii7/AridTag/RSC-1.jpg[/img]
As you can see I am now IN GAME :)
Obviously theres tons of bugs and shit but fuck...I made it in game :D
